President Donald Trump has announced his intent to nominate Justin George Muzinich as the Deputy Secretary of the Treasury. Muzinich currently serves as Counselor to the Secretary of the Treasury and advises on domestic and international policy initiatives, including tax reform. He previously worked as the President of Muzinich & Co., an international investment firm, and taught at Columbia Business School. Muzinich holds a J.D. from Yale Law School, an M.B.A. from Harvard Business School, and a B.A. from Harvard.

Additionally, Duane C. Caneva has been nominated to be the Chief Medical Officer of the Department of Homeland Security. Dr. Caneva is an emergency medicine physician who previously served as the Director of Medical Preparedness Policy at the National Security Council. He has experience in roles within the United States Navy, White House, Department of Homeland Security, and Department of State. Dr. Caneva received his Bachelor of Arts in Chemistry and Doctor of Medicine from the University of Chicago, as well as a Master of Science in National Security Strategy from the National War College.